      "comment": "ALLERGY FREE (1) has been out of the placings at his last couple of runs but turned heads when posting a flying 18.78 over 330m at this track three starts back. Should be in this for a long way. ZIPPING WHEELER (2) looks overdue for a win having finished in the minors at her last three runs, the latest when second (26.04) at this track. Has never been out of the money in three starts this distance. Rates a winning chance on best. PELOPONNESE (5) struggled to get involved last start after settling off pace at Wentworth Park, but prior to that won by 2.25 lengths at Goulburn (24.71) beating Magic Linkin in a Grade 4/5 on January 30. Key player if finds best. LEONI BALE (7) is likely to have admirers.",
